<section id="schema">
  <div class="sh"><div class="sh-n">04</div><div class="sh-t">The ClickHouse schema — better than GA4, yours forever</div></div>
  <div class="schema-wrap">
    <div class="schema-grid">
      <div class="schema-l">
        <h2 class="schema-h">The canonical<br />event schema.<br /><em>Yours. No sampling.</em></h2>
        <p class="schema-p">GA4 samples data at scale. BigQuery exports cost money and lag. Segment takes a cut of every event and shares it with its data partners. ClickHouse gives you sub-second queries over billions of events on a $50/month server.</p>
        <p class="schema-p">The Attestrack canonical schema is designed for the queries that actually matter: funnel analysis by consent state, attribution across ad networks using your own first-party data, anomaly detection when something breaks, and session replay correlation without a third-party tool.</p>
        <p class="schema-p"><strong>Every field is documented. The materialized views are included. The query library is open source.</strong> You're not adopting a black box — you're adopting a schema you can read, fork, and extend.</p>
        <div class="schema-caps">
          <div class="schema-cap"><div class="sc-n">&lt;1ms</div><div class="sc-l">ClickHouse query latency on 1B+ rows</div></div>
          <div class="schema-cap"><div class="sc-n">0</div><div class="sc-l">Data sharing with third parties</div></div>
          <div class="schema-cap"><div class="sc-n">100%</div><div class="sc-l">Of events captured — no sampling</div></div>
          <div class="schema-cap"><div class="sc-n">MIT</div><div class="sc-l">License — fork it, extend it, own it</div></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="schema-r">
        <div class="schema-r-intro">tracking_events — canonical schema (ClickHouse DDL)</div>
        <div class="code">
          <pre set:html={`<span class="cb">CREATE TABLE</span> <span class="cg">tracking_events</span> (
  event_id             <span class="co">UUID</span>,
  site_id              <span class="co">String</span>,
  session_id           <span class="co">String</span>,       <span class="cd">-- opaque</span>
  event_type           <span class="co">String</span>,       <span class="cd">-- page_view|purchase|etc</span>
  event_name           <span class="co">String</span>,
  timestamp            <span class="co">DateTime64(3, 'UTC')</span>,
  page_url             <span class="co">String</span>,
  page_path            <span class="co">String</span>,
  referrer             <span class="co">String</span>,

  <span class="cd">-- UTM parameters</span>
  utm_source           <span class="co">String</span>,
  utm_medium           <span class="co">String</span>,
  utm_campaign         <span class="co">String</span>,
  utm_content          <span class="co">String</span>,
  utm_term             <span class="co">String</span>,

  <span class="cd">-- Attribution</span>
  ad_network           <span class="co">String</span>,
  ad_campaign_id       <span class="co">String</span>,
  ad_adset_id          <span class="co">String</span>,
  ad_ad_id             <span class="co">String</span>,

  <span class="cd">-- Consent — documented, not gated</span>
  consent_state        <span class="co">String</span>,       <span class="cd">-- GRANTED|DENIED|GPC_DENIED</span>
  consent_categories   <span class="co">Array(String)</span>,
  gpc_signal           <span class="co">Boolean</span>,

  <span class="cd">-- Conversion data</span>
  value                <span class="co">Decimal(10,2)</span>,
  currency             <span class="co">String</span>,
  order_id             <span class="co">String</span>,

  <span class="cd">-- Device</span>
  device_type          <span class="co">String</span>,
  browser              <span class="co">String</span>,
  country              <span class="co">String</span>,

  <span class="cd">-- System</span>
  banner_version       <span class="co">String</span>,
  jurisdiction         <span class="co">String</span>,
  shadow_mode          <span class="co">Boolean</span>,
  date                 <span class="co">Date</span>  <span class="co">MATERIALIZED</span> toDate(timestamp)
)
<span class="cb">ENGINE</span> = MergeTree()
<span class="cb">PARTITION BY</span> toYYYYMM(date)
<span class="cb">ORDER BY</span> (site_id, timestamp, event_id);`} />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

